img.alt: Nike Kobe 11 Brave Blue/Metallic Silver-University Blue 2016 For Sale

div.p: The Brave Blue colorway of the Kobe 11 sticks true to the original and utilizes a Flyknit upper instead of the engineered mesh we’ll see on the Aces colorway tomorrow. Looking at this Brave Blue colorway we can see that it features a gradient Flyknit upper that starts off with Brave Blue on the toe and then shifts to University Blue at the heel. University Blue also lands on the laces and the Kobe branding on the tongue. Metallic Silver provides some contrast as it can be seen on the Swoosh logos on the side panels. It is being said that this colorway of the Kobe 11 is inspired by Eric Avar, the man who design Kobe’s Nike sneakers.

div.p:
The unique colorway pairs a pristine white Flyknit base with multicolor threading woven into the midfoot while white leather Swooshes are stitched above. This version also adds heel tabs, which we haven’t seen on the previous releases.
Nike gave us an official name and it’s now being known a the Kobe 11 Elite White Horse. Why White Horse? Well the only explanation that Nike gave on this colorway is as follows, ‘The latest iteration salutes the Black Mamba in winning fashion with callouts to the league legend.’ So this Kobe 11 pretty much is a nod to Kobe’s winning ways.

h1.a: Nike Kobe 11 Elite “Mark Parker” Black/Metallic Gold-Blue Lagoon-Action Green

img.alt: Nike Kobe 11 Elite "Mark Parker" Black/Metallic Gold-Blue Lagoon-Action Green

div.p:
he CEO of Nike created what many may consider the very best offering within the trio of designs for the Kobe 11 by himself, Tinker Hatfield , and Eric Avar, featuring the shoe in mix of black and purple Flyknit with a textured snakeskin panel on the heels for a bold yet sophisticated look. The third and final installment of the Nike Kobe 11 “Muse” Pack is finally revealed through this tribute to Nike CEO Mark Parker. Kobe Bryant has always viewed Parker as a personal mentor, viewing his pensiveness and calm as a key aspect to his decision-making skills. There’s no doubt that Parker’s influence on Kobe has translated in some ways to his success on and off the court, which is why Nike closes out this amazing collection with this necessary homage.
The Nike Kobe 11 Elite “Muse” pack concludes tomorrow with the launch of Mark Parker’s tribute to the Black Mamba. Joining the interpretation of the Kobe 11 by Eric Avar and Tinker Hatfield, Parker’s version features a unique black and royal blue speckled Flyknit upper with snake textured leather panels at each heel. The sole also features a unique treatment, with solid white up top that reveals a transition to clear on the bottom with stripes visible underneath.
